# raycast-contacts

A Raycast extension that searches Apple Contacts (macOS native) with a full detail view.

## What it does

- Single command: **Search Contacts** — searches all Apple Contacts via AppleScript
- List view and Detail view (toggleable via dropdown; default is Detail)
- Detail panel shows: phones, emails, addresses, birthday, notes
- Actions: Open in Contacts app, Compose Email, Call, Copy name/email/phone, Refresh

## Architecture

```
src/
  search-contacts.tsx      ← command entry point
  apple-contacts.ts        ← Two-phase JXA fetcher via osascript -l JavaScript
                              fetchAppleContacts()  — bulk list (fast, ~0.4s)
                              fetchContactDetail()  — single contact full info
  hooks.ts                 ← useCachedPromise wrapper (useContacts)
  types.ts                 ← UnifiedContact, ContactField, ContactAddress
  helpers.ts               ← groupByLetter, formatBirthday
  components/
    ContactList.tsx        ← List view (name + company only at list level)
    ContactDetail.tsx      ← Full detail screen, fetches emails/phones on push
    ContactActions.tsx     ← ActionPanel for list items (See Details, Copy Name, Open)
```

## Key implementation details

- **Two-phase loading**: list fetch is bulk JXA (name/id/company only, ~0.4s). Per-contact
  detail (emails, phones, addresses, birthday, notes) fetched via `whose { id: ... }` on demand.
- Uses `osascript -l JavaScript` (JXA) via Node.js `child_process.execFile` — NOT AppleScript
- Apple Contact labels come through as `_$!<Mobile>!$_` — `formatType()` strips this everywhere
- `useCachedPromise` from `@raycast/utils` caches between sessions (instant on subsequent opens)
- Per-contact detail is also cached by `useCachedPromise` in `ContactDetail`

## Dev workflow

```bash
npm run dev     # live-reload in Raycast
npm run build   # production build to dist/
npm run lint    # ESLint via @raycast/eslint-config
```

